<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; PUBLIC 
WORKS BOARD CHIEF QUITS TO JOIN HAHN'S STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a high-level City Hall restructuring, Charles Dickerson, president of the 
city's powerful Board of Public Works, announced his resignation Thursday to 
become a special assistant to City Atty. James Hahn. 
</P>
<P>
 Dickerson, formerly a private attorney, was named by Mayor Richard Riordan 
last year to the five-member board, which wields strong influence on everything 
from filming permits to sewer construction. 
</P>
<P>
 Sources said that Dickerson will probably be replaced by Ellen Stein, a member 
of the Animal Regulation Commission and the wife of mayoral adviser Ted Stein. 
</P>
<P>
 Hahn also named Evan Braude, a former prosecutor and Long Beach councilman, as 
a top aide. Braude will handle transportation and environmental matters in the 
city attorney's office, while Dickerson will focus on economic development and 
risk management. 
</P>
