<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEMOCRACY AT WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Recent polls seem to indicate that many of us are unaware that the Clinton 
Administration is giving us the best demonstration of democracy at work in the 
history of the American presidency. 
</P>
<P>
 When have we seen a President engage with such intelligence and zeal in 
continuous persuasion and public debate on almost a daily basis? 
</P>
<P>
 Under what administrations of recent memory have we seen such extensive 
disclosure and public discussion in the media of major legislative issues? 
</P>
<P>
 When have we seen a President so willing to accommodate other points of view, 
to subordinate partisan political advantage in order to reach mutually 
agreeable solutions? 
</P>
<P>
 Those who label Clinton "a wimp," "indecisive," "wishy-washy," only reveal 
their frustration with the inevitable compromises of our deliberative process. 
Mistakes, miscalculations, past bad behavior notwithstanding, this President's 
commitment to truly democratic leadership has seldom been matched. 
</P>
<P>
 HAROLD GOULD 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
