</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 49-year-old Ventura man died Thursday of head injuries a week after he was 
struck by a car while walking through traffic on Victoria Avenue, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Faulkner had been hospitalized in the intensive care unit of the 
Ventura County Medical Center since the accident on Aug. 31, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Faulkner was hit after he walked through traffic on Victoria Avenue near 
California 126, Ventura County Coroner Jim Wingate said.  
</P>
<P>
 "Evidently two or three cars missed him and he was hit by a car and a light 
truck," Wingate said. Faulkner was pronounced dead Thursday at 1:40 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Faulkner lived with various friends in Ventura and is survived by a sister, 
Barbara Courtenanche, of Hydesville, Calif., Wingate said. 
</P>
<P>
 Faulkner, who was also known as Richard Outland, was the adopted son of the 
late Charles Outland, a noted Ventura County author and journalist from Santa 
Paula, according to Hazel Outland, Charles Outland's sister-in-law. JASON GRANT 
