<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; INDUSTRIAL LEAGUE BACKS BASE AS AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Industrial League of Orange County on Thursday endorsed Measure A, the 
county initiative on the November ballot that calls for the conversion of the 
El Toro Marine Corps Air Station into a commercial airport. 
</P>
<P>
 "An expanded airport is essential to the county's economic health, and there 
are no other viable sites," league officials said in a statement released 
Wednesday."A commercial airport at El Toro . . . could stimulate an economic 
boom in Orange County." 
</P>
<P>
 The league is made up of leaders from 850 manufacturing, high-tech, aerospace 
and financial firms. 
</P>
<P>
 The ballot measure is opposed by many residents from South County cities who 
fear turning El Toro in a commercial airport after the military pulls out at 
the end of the decade will increase noise, traffic and pollution. 
</P>
<P>
 The county has formed a joint powers authority along with several cities to 
create a reuse plan for the base. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
