<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; PERMIT REAPPLICATION ORDINANCE WEIGHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business owners who were denied a city permit to operate may have to wait a 
year before reapplying.  
</P>
<P>
 The City Council this week introduced an ordinance that would impose the 
waiting period when a business permit is rejected.The council is expected to 
give final adoption of the ordinance at its Sept. 20 meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, if a business permit is denied, there could be a reapplication 
within a month or two, even sooner, said Donald L. Heinbuch, administrative 
services manager. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, Heinbuch said the waiting period gives the city a break since 
there is an extensive application process for these special business permits. 
There is a detailed application, investigation and hearing process for business 
permits such as bingo, massage, pawnbrokers, billiard halls and other 
businesses that require special investigations. 
</P>
<P>
 But those procedures do not specify a waiting period after denial before a new 
application can be submitted. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
