<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 6 SPOTS AVAILABLE ON 3 MUNICIPAL BOARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking volunteers to serve on three municipal boards. 
</P>
<P>
 There is one vacancy on the Human Resources Board, which serves to enhance 
communication and coordination among the various agencies, organizations and 
individuals that provide human services to residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fourth of July Board has four open positions. The board is responsible for 
raising money and coordinating the city's annual Fourth of July parade and 
related festivities. 
</P>
<P>
 The Finance Board has one vacancy. The board reviews and makes recommendations 
regarding fiscal policies, annual financial audit, debt management and other 
financial issues. 
</P>
<P>
 Persons applying to serve on the board should have extensive financial 
experience or have a serious interest in municipal budgets. The City Council 
will make the appointment Oct. 3. Applications are available by calling Pat 
Jones at (714) 536-5203. 
</P>
<P>
 For the other two board positions, information is available by calling (714) 
536-5496. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are also available at City Hall, 2000 Main St. 
</P>
</TEXT>
