<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 28 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 5. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 357. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 312. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: 
</P>
<P>
 $123.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by 
</P>
<P>
 owners: $238 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Players presented their "concept" during a 30-minute 
evening session at the commissioner's office. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "I'm excited that we're talking again, but that excitement wanes 
when you look at the amount of work we have to do. We're at a pressure point. 
Time is running out." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Orel Hershiser, Dodger pitcher 
