<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; HARRISON LIMPS AFTER WORKOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rams released wide receiver Todd Kinchen because they couldn't keep him 
injury-free and signed former Falcon wide receiver Tony Harrison for their 
practice squad as a replacement. After one workout, Harrison began limping. 
</P>
<P>
 "What happened, and this is amazing," Coach Chuck Knox said, "he woke up and 
he had this pain in the hip. 
</P>
<P>
 "He ran well out here (Wednesday). In fact, he was impressive for the first 
workout." 
</P>
<P>
 Harrison, who was limping badly, left after practice to undergo medical 
examination. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 After all the trouble the Rams have gone through to get permission for 
cornerback Darryl Henley to play for them, Knox won't say now if he will. 
</P>
<P>
 Henley has been cleared to join the team for Sunday's game against the Falcons 
in Atlanta, and Knox has watched him practice without problems the last two 
days, but was noncommittal Thursday. "We'll make a decision on who our 45 
players will be on Sunday an hour and 15 minutes before the ballgame," Knox 
said. T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
