<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; ALHAMBRA GIVES GLENDALE MOOR THAN IT CAN HANDLE, 
28-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As far as debuts go, Ted Clarke's was somewhat forgettable. 
</P>
<P>
 Clarke, who took over as football coach at Glendale High early in the summer, 
watched his Dynamiters lose to Alhambra, 28-14, Thursday night at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Alhambra broke out to a 21-0 first-half lead and coasted in the nonleague 
opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Moor quarterback Aryn Hart completed nine of 13 passes for 160 yards and a 
pair of touchdowns to Danny Harrison. 
</P>
<P>
 "The combination of our youth and (playing against) a good passing team, 
that's tough," Clarke said. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale was also flagged 11 times for 95 yards in penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 "That was a coaching problem," Clarke said. "There's also some youth in the 
coach." 
</P>
<P>
 After Alhambra's quick start, the game was never in question. 
</P>
<P>
 Moor running back Patrick Nieves complemented Hart's passing with 87 yards in 
eight carries. 
</P>
<P>
 His 46-yard touchdown run gave Alhambra a 14-0 first-quarter lead. Nieves also 
returned the second-half kickoff 82 yards for a touchdown and a 28-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Backup running back Jason Klintworth paced Glendale with 86 yards in nine 
carries. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dynamiters rebounded from the Moors' third touchdown when Benjamin Malen 
returned the ensuing kickoff 87 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Nieves' return to open the third quarter sealed it. 
</P>
<P>
 The Moors ran only six plays in the first quarter, but rolled up 115 total 
yards and a 14-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 On their third play from scrimmage, quarterback Hart connected with wide-open 
receiver Danny Harrison on a 24-yard touchdown play. 
</P>
<P>
 After Nieves' scoring run late in the quarter, Hart and Harrison combined for 
a score in the second quarter, this one measuring 14 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale answered when Malen broke free, but the extra point was blocked by 
Mike Navarrette, and the Dynamiters trailed, 21-6. 
</P>
<P>
 After Nieves' return made it 28-6, Glendale running back Mauricio Pena scored 
on a two-yard run late in the game and Klintworth added a two-point conversion 
to close out the scoring. Football Top 10 
</P>
<P>
 Selected by sportswriters of The Times 04,04,13,14,08 Rk Team League W-L 1 
Sylmar East Valley 10-2-1 2 Ant. Valley Golden 7-6 3 Hart Foothill 10-2 4 Royal 
Marmonte 6-5 5 Westlake Marmonte 8-3-1 6 Taft North Valley 10-2 7 Notre Dame 
Mission 10-3 8 Ventura Channel 8-3 9 Crespi Del Rey 8-5 10 Saugus Foothill 5-4 
DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
