<P>
SHEPHERD'S SCORES HELP ARCADIA TOP SADDLEBACK, 21-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jon Shepherd rushed for 166 yards and two second-half touchdowns as Arcadia 
defeated Saddleback, 21-7, Thursday night at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 On the third play of the third quarter, Shepherd broke through the middle of 
the Saddleback defense for a 66-yard touchdown run, giving Arcadia a 14-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Arcadia's larger linemen wore down Saddleback in the second half, as the 
Apaches outgained the Roadrunners, 157-49 yards. Shepherd had 109 yards rushing 
in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 He capped the scoring with an eight-yard touchdown run on the first play of 
the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (0-1) had a chance to get back in the game midway through the third 
quarter, when Morrow Potts sacked Arcadia quarterback Matt Shepherd, forcing a 
fumble that was recovered by the Roadrunners' Rafael Lucero, who returned it to 
the Arcadia 44-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 But on the next play, Saddleback's Brian Killingbeck threw an interception 
that Frank Liu returned 39 yards to the Saddleback 42. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback's lone touchdown came in the first quarter, when Killingbeck threw 
an eight-yard touchdown pass to Hector Hernandez. 
</P>
<P>
 Killingbeck completed three of 10 passes for 38 yards. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
