<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGNOLIA'S MARIN GIVES SANTIAGO HEAVY POUNDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEORGE WHITEMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carlos Marin, a 220-pound running back/linebacker, pounded through Santiago 
for two short-yardage touchdowns to lead Magnolia to a 21-0 victory Thursday 
night at Garden Grove High. 
</P>
<P>
 Marin scored a one-yard run in the first quarter and a two-yard run in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Eliescu finished the scoring with his own two-yard run in the fourth 
quarter. He rushed for 46 yards in 11 carries. Marin finished with 20 yards in 
six carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Robert Nicols completed seven of 10 passes for 82 yards for 
Magnolia. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sentinel defense held the Cavaliers to minus 20 yards rushing and 20 
passing. 
</P>
<P>
 Cavalier quarterback Octavio Villa completed two of 14 passes with three 
interceptions -- the last coming as the time expired. He was also sacked three 
times. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean Roy led Magnolia with 75 yards rushing in 16 carries. GEORGE WHITEMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
