<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; NO. 1 STANFORD BEATS UCI IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Stanford defeated UC Irvine, 9-5, in a Mountain Pacific Sports 
Federation water polo game Thursday at Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was very pleased with our effort," Anteater Coach Ted Newland said."It was 
close all the way and the score does not reflect how we played. We are a very 
young team. I'm not disappointed at all." 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine (0-1, 0-1), ranked fifth in national coaches' poll, took a 2-0 lead, 
but Stanford came back with three goals to lead, 3-2, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine pulled within one, 5-4, on a goal by Matt Maunz early in the fourth, 
but the Cardinal scored two quick goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Omar Amr, a Sunny Hills High graduate, scored two goals for the Anteaters and 
Maunz also had two. Redshirt freshman Tom Davis played well, getting nine saves 
in goal for Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters will next compete in the Newport SeaFest Southern California 
tournament at Corona del Mar High on Saturday. They face Air Force at 8:10 a.m. 
and California at 12:50. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Christian 3, Christian Heritage 1 -- Ryan Bean scored three goals to 
lead Pacific Christian College (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 6, Whittier 1 -- The Vanguards scored four goals 
in 17 minutes of the second half to defeat Whittier (0-3). Chris Shaparro and 
Jorge Perez, from Santa Ana High, each scored two goals. Jesus Miramontes and 
Kevin Villar each added one for the Vanguards (1-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
