<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; PLOOG'S 8 GOALS LEAD LA HABRA IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Habra's Dan Ploog scored eight goals to lead his team to an 11-3 victory 
over Katella in an opening-round games of the Bell Gardens water polo 
tournament Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra scored all of its goals in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 In an earlier game, Ploog scored four in a 22-2 victory over La Verne Damien. 
Dave Ploog also scored four goals in that game. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 14 1/3, Loara 6 2/3 -- Linhthuy Dihn and Linda Cao swept at No. 2 
doubles, 6-4, 6-3, 6-0, for Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 18, Fountain Valley 0 -- The Monarchs lost only eleven games in 
their victory over Fountain Valley. Laura Ruben won at No. 1 singles, 6-1, 6-0, 
6-0, and Sarah Jarrett swept, 6-0, 6-0, 6-1, at No. 2 for Mater Dei (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 14, Connelly 4 -- Sisters Ly and Hanh Kim swept their singles sets for 
Savanna. 
</P>
<P>
 Western 18, Buena Park 0 -- Debbie Jethva swept in No. 1 singles, 6-0, 6-0, 
6-0, and teammates Rie Sasaki and Susy Yoon won in doubles, 6-0, 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 16, La Habra 2 -- Junior Erin Kubota won at No. 1 singles, 6-4, 6-1, 
6-4, for Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 3, Whittier California 2 -- Moira Wolfrum and Debbie Yau both had 
11 kills each in the 6-15, 15-11, 12-15, 15-11, 15-2 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 3, Walnut 0 -- Ann Marie Hatchel had six kills and Shannon 
Breazeale had five to help Brea-Olinda to a 15-12, 15-7, 15-5 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 3, Trabuco Hills 0 -- Nicole Terry had 14 kills for El Modena, which 
defeated Trabuco Hills, 15-8, 15-5, 15-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 3, Westminster 0 -- Misty Thompson had ten aces and 19 assists in 
the season opener for Laguna Hills. The Hawks won 15-4, 15-5, 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 3, Katella 0 -- Charlene Conley had eight kills to lead Orange, in a 
15-0, 15-5, 15-10 victory. 
</P>
