<P>
 Fixed-Rate Mortgages Rise: Thirty-year, fixed-rate mortgages averaged 8.51% 
this week, up from 8.48% last week, according to a national survey by the 
Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. It was the highest since Aug. 25, when the 
average was 8.56%.The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% last October. 
Fifteen-year mortgages averaged 8.03% this week, up from 7.96% a week earlier. 
The rates do not include add-on fees known as points. 
