non-prescription forms next Feb. 22. The agency has received reports of adverse 
reactions, including deaths, disablement and hospitalization. The consumer 
group contends the prescription form is just as dangerous and should be removed 
from the market immediately. It is sold under the brand name Quinamm as well as 
in several generic versions. 
