<P>
 GTE Seeks Contel Shares It Doesn't Own: The company offered to buy the 10% 
stake of Contel Cellular Inc. held by the public for $22.50 per share, a 
proposal with an overall value of $224 million. GTE Corp. acquired the other 
90% of the company as part of its $6.6-billion merger with Contel Corp. in 
1991.Contel Cellular's stock rose 32% on the news. It finished up $5.75 at 
$23.50 in Nasdaq trading. GTE finished up 12.5 cents at $30.875 on the New York 
Stock Exchange. Following the merger, GTE's cellular business, the nation's 
second-largest with 1.9 million customers, will be operated under the name GTE 
Mobilnet. Contel Cellular accounts for 621,000 customers of that total. It owns 
systems in 32 cities and acts as a limited partner for systems in 27 other 
cities and 59 rural service areas. 
