PRESIDENT-CEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Charles A. Laverty has been hired as president and chief executive officer 
of Davstar Industries Ltd., a Costa Mesa manufacturer of disposable medical 
plastic products. Laverty takes over positions relinquished by Davstar's 
chairman, Jerry Silver, who will concentrate on new products and further growth 
through acquisitions.Laverty, 49, who was hired after a three-month search, 
comes with a reputation of being able to spur a company's growth, Silver said. 
The new president is expected to help Davstar increase sales of its existing 
product line, Silver said. Laverty was chairman, president and chief executive 
of Curaflex Health Services Inc. in Ontario and helped to merge that company 
with three others in July to form Coram Healthcare Corp., which is temporarily 
based in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * John W. Adams has been appointed chairman and chief executive of Regency 
Health Services Inc., a Tustin operator of specialty health-care facilities. He 
succeeds Cecil Mays, a co-founder of the company, who is retiring from 
day-to-day involvement with the company after its merger with Care Enterprises 
Inc. He will remain a member of the Regency board of directors. Adams is the 
former chairman and chief executive of Care Enterprises. Richard K. Matros, 
president and chief operating officer of Regency, will succeed Mays as a member 
of the executive committee of the Regency board. 
</P>
<P>
 * Philip A. Edwards has been appointed managing director of Platinum U.K., a 
wholly owned subsidiary of Irvine-based Platinum Software Corp. Edwards 
succeeds Ronald Drake, who has left the company.  
</P>
<P>
 Before coming to Platinum, Edwards was managing director of Agility 
Software/Baan International Ltd., a software distribution company he founded in 
1992. In 1993, Edwards merged Agility Software with two other distributorships 
to form Baan International. 
</P>
